comments: Only northern Mexico sampled so no lineage info where we have camera trap data
Well sampled when combining info from all three papers. But some polygons in plains not sampled so ignore those
Mexico not sampled but very likely the same lineage as western. Ignore polygons are small
No samples in Canada, Washington state, or southern California. Sort of a complicated one with multiple lineages and hard to tell exactly where to draw breaks
Ignore polygons are small and on east coast
Small part of range sampled and sample size is small. May not be useful - no overlap with camera data
Center of range sampled but southern, western, and northeastern part of range not sampled
Ignore observations in midwest and east. Also no need to draw a break because the two lineages are disjunct

Complicated one: IUCN doesn't include ABC island part of range but drew split there anyway because there are iNat observations there. IUCN range includes the Fremont squirrel range but we should ignore that given it's a different species
Mexico not sampled. It's likely mostly western but could also be a different lineage
